'''Richard Cockett''' (born 1961)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aim25.ac.uk/cats/1/2828.htm |title=Richard Cockett|accessdate=27 July 2014 |publisher=British Library of Political and Economic Science }}</ref> is a British historian, journalist and writer.<ref name="economist">{{cite web |url=http://www.economist.com/mediadirectory/richard-cockett |title=Profile of Richard Cockett |publisher=[[The Economist]] |accessdate=27 July 2014}}</ref>

He is a regional editor of [[The Economist]], with experience in Mexico, Central America, Africa<ref name="opendemocracy">{{cite web |url=https://www.opendemocracy.net/author/richard-cockett |title=Profile of Richard Cockett |publisher=Open Democracy}}</ref> and Singapore.<ref name="economist"/> He was previously a senior lecturer in politics and history at [[Royal Holloway, University of London]].<ref name="opendemocracy"/>

== Selected works ==
