{{Infobox person | name = Virginia M. Mecklenburg | image = Virginia Mecklenburg on 5 Feb 2015.JPG | alt = | caption = Virginia Mecklenburg standing in front of the painting Artist on WPA by Moses Soyer at the Smithsonian American Art Museum on 5 February 2015. | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = American | other_names = | occupation = Senior Curator of painting and sculpture | known_for = Published works regarding the art and lives of artists such as [[Edward Hopper]], [[Frederick Carl Frieseke]], [[George Bellows]], and others }}
'''Virginia McCord Mecklenburg''' (born November 11, 1946) is the Senior Curator of painting and sculpture at the [[Smithsonian American Art Museum]]. She has been a curator at the [[Smithsonian]] since 1979 and has organized more than twenty exhibits. Additionally, she has published works regarding the art and lives of artists such as [[Edward Hopper]], [[Frederick Carl Frieseke]], [[George Bellows]], and others.
==Some published works== * Edward Hopper's Houses, ''Magazine Antiques'', 11/1/99 by Virginia M. Mecklenburg * New York City and the Ashcan school - American art movement, ''Magazine Antiques'', 11/1/95 by Virginia M. Mecklenburg
